{"TopicId":216292,"ForumId":197,"TopicTitle":"CommNet not working.","CreatedByName":"raver20999","CreatedById":54555,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-07T18:38:51Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"raver20999","CreatedById":54555,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-07T18:38:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn my game I set up 3 satellites with RA-100 antennas at geostationary orbit. One has line of sight to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E and the remaining 2 have line of sight to the one pointed at \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E. No matter what antenna I put on a probe as soon as I engage the last stage of the spacecraft (with no kerbins onboard) the probe loses comms. Has anyone else had this issue?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"raver20999","CreatedById":54555,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-07T18:58:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry just read the post about report bugs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022background-color:rgb(249,249,249);\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003EKSP Version: 0.1.1.0.21572\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003EOperating System and version\u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E Windows 11, Version 22H2\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003EPC Specs:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003ECPU: Ryzen 7 5700X\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003EGPU: EVGA\u00A0RTX 2080\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003ERAM: 32GB 3200 MHz\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDescription of the bug:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECommNet connection maintaining after staging the last stage for probe only spacecraft.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003ECommNet connection lost after staging\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESteps to Replicate: (This is what I did in my game but whatever CommNet setup will do it.)\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHave 3 satellites with RA-100 antennas in geostationary orbit. All three needs to have line of sight to each other and one needs to be line of sight to Kerbal Space Center.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWhen I create a rocket I have one stage for the 3400 m/s needed to get to orbit.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cb style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:16px;\u0022\u003EThe second stage is the space stage which finalizes the orbit, \u003C/b\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003Emaneuvers\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cb style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u00A0the probe (usually a section of a space station), docks the section, and deorbits itself to reduce space debris.\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cb style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u00A0This second stage has its own probe and antennas so it can stay connected.\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cb style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:16px;\u0022\u003EAs soon as I decouple the space stage from the station so I can deorbit it the space craft loses its CommNet Connection.\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFixes / Workarounds:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EClosing/saving the game and restarting the game.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EA list of ALL mods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENone\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOther Notes / Screenshots / Log Files (if possible..)\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\nNone\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Beyond_Earth_Orbit","CreatedById":228548,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-10T15:20:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAn alternative workaround to closing the game outright seems to be a quick save and a quick load, though it doesn\u0027t always seem to work if you have multiple probes in the same area of influence and you may have to quick save and reload each time you switch to another one.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}